  "response": "To learn CPT (Current Procedural Terminology) online, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Official AMA Resources\n- Purchase CPT Professional Manual from American Medical Association (AMA)\n- Take online courses through AMA's website\n- Access AMA's CPT resources and training materials\n\n2. Online Learning Platforms\n- Udemy\n- Coursera\n- edX\n- LinkedIn Learning\n- Offer medical coding and CPT certification courses\n\n3. Professional Organizations\n- AAPC (American Academy of Professional Coders)\n- AHIMA (American Health Information Management Association)\n- Provide online training, webinars, and certification programs\n\n4. Free/Low-Cost Options\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Medical coding blogs\n- WebMD educational resources\n- Medical coding forums\n\n5. Community College Online Courses\n- Many community colleges offer online medical coding programs\n- Provide comprehensive CPT training\n\n6. Self-Study Methods\n- Use CPT codebooks\n- Practice coding scenarios\n- Take online practice exams\n- Watch instructional videos\n\n7. Certification Preparation\n- Prepare for professional certifications like CPC\n- Take practice tests\n- Study exam preparation materials\n\nChoose methods that suit your learning style, budget, and schedule.",
